In this article, President Trump delivers remarks during a wreath-laying ceremony at Yad Vashem, the Holocaust memorial in Jerusalem. He honors the memory of the six million Jews who were murdered during the Holocaust and acknowledges the immense evil and destruction that took place. Trump emphasizes the importance of remembering and mourning the lives lost, and the duty to prevent such a tragedy from happening again. He praises the resilience and success of the Jewish people and reaffirms the commitment to the State of Israel. Trump concludes by expressing sadness for the lives lost, determination to keep their memories alive, and the resolve to confront evil. He asks for strength, wisdom, and courage to chart a righteous path.